								<!-- bodycontent -->
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="dablink">"Ethnicity" and "Peoples" redirect here. For other uses, see <a href="Ethnicity_(disambiguation)" title="Ethnicity (disambiguation)">Ethnicity (disambiguation)</a> and <a href="Peoples_(disambiguation)" title="Peoples (disambiguation)" class="mw-redirect">Peoples (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Modern_Han_Chinese_in_Ming_Attire.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b1/Modern_Han_Chinese_in_Ming_Attire.jpg/220px-Modern_Han_Chinese_in_Ming_Attire.jpg" width="220" height="152" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b1/Modern_Han_Chinese_in_Ming_Attire.jpg/330px-Modern_Han_Chinese_in_Ming_Attire.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b1/Modern_Han_Chinese_in_Ming_Attire.jpg/440px-Modern_Han_Chinese_in_Ming_Attire.jpg 2x" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Modern_Han_Chinese_in_Ming_Attire.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf8/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
With over 1.2 billion people, <a href="Han_Chinese" title="Han Chinese">Han Chinese</a> is the largest ethnic group in the world.</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Pashtuns.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/91/Pashtuns.jpg/220px-Pashtuns.jpg" width="220" height="196" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/91/Pashtuns.jpg/330px-Pashtuns.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/91/Pashtuns.jpg/440px-Pashtuns.jpg 2x" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Pashtuns.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf8/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
<a href="Pashtun_people" title="Pashtun people">Pashtun people</a> of the <a href="Pashtunistan" title="Pashtunistan">Pashtunistan</a> region, which sits in an area between south of the <a href="Hindu_Kush" title="Hindu Kush">Hindu Kush</a> in <a href="Afghanistan" title="Afghanistan">Afghanistan</a> and the <a href="Indus_River" title="Indus River">Indus River</a> in <a href="Pakistan" title="Pakistan">Pakistan</a>. They number around 50 million.</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:KorowaiHombre01.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/90/KorowaiHombre01.jpg/220px-KorowaiHombre01.jpg" width="220" height="293" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/90/KorowaiHombre01.jpg/330px-KorowaiHombre01.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/90/KorowaiHombre01.jpg/440px-KorowaiHombre01.jpg 2x" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:KorowaiHombre01.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf8/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
<a href="Korowai_people" title="Korowai people">Korowai people</a> of <a href="Papua_(province)" title="Papua (province)">Papua</a> numbered just around 3,000 people, and was <a href="Uncontacted_people" title="Uncontacted people" class="mw-redirect">uncontacted</a> until 1970s.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Ethnicity</b> or <b>ethnic group</b> is a socially defined <a href="Social_group" title="Social group">category</a> based on common <a href="Culture" title="Culture">culture</a> or <a href="Nationality" title="Nationality">nationality</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> Ethnicity can, but does not have to, include common <a href="Common_ancestry" title="Common ancestry" class="mw-redirect">ancestry</a>, <a href="Human_appearance" title="Human appearance" class="mw-redirect">appearance</a>, <a href="Cuisine" title="Cuisine">cuisine</a>, <a href="Dress" title="Dress">dressing</a> style, <a href="Cultural_heritage" title="Cultural heritage">heritage</a>, <a href="History" title="History">history</a>, <a href="Language" title="Language">language</a> or <a href="Dialect" title="Dialect">dialect</a>, <a href="Religion" title="Religion">religion</a>, <a href="Symbols" title="Symbols" class="mw-redirect">symbols</a>, <a href="Tradition" title="Tradition">traditions</a>, or other cultural factor. Ethnic identity is constantly reinforced through common characteristics which set the group apart from other groups.<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-Anderson.2C_4-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Anderson.2C-4"><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-ethnic2_5-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-ethnic2-5"><span>[</span>5<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-6"><span>[</span>6<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-Smith_7-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Smith-7"><span>[</span>7<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
